h3. Issue Summary

If the filter applied to the board has any wrong element set as, for example, a Component or/and another field which was renamed or deleted, this affects inline issue creation through Backlog.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create an Epic issue;
 # Create a Component and apply this to the just created Epic issue;
 # Add the just created component to the query of the filter that is applied to the board;
 # Delete or rename this Component;
 # On Backlog of the board, select any version AND an Epic;
 # Click on the inline issue creation feature.
 # The Epic Link and Fix version values won't be automatically populated as expected

h3. Expected Results

Since a version and Epic issue is selected in version and Epic panels, those values should be automatically populated in the Create Issue dialog.
h3. Actual Results

The values are not being automatically populated:

!image-2020-09-15-12-55-35-258.png|width=443,height=466!

A 400 message is shown in Browser dev tools as a response:
{code:java}
{"errorMessages":["The value 'newcomponent' does not exist for the field 'component'."],"errors":{}} {code}
It's the same message that appears for the filter:

!image-2020-09-15-12-55-13-457.png|width=1008,height=129!

Since no error message is shown in Backlog UI, this might turn troubleshooting process more difficult.
h3. Workaround

Review the filter that is applied to the board and correct any wrong element it might have. As soon as the filter is fixed, the values should be automatically populated when creating an issue
